The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional neural networks for image processing tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also draws inspiration from partial differential equations (PDEs) and uses PDE theory to derive new neural network architectures, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges associated with deep ResNets and proposes new architectures, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents numerical experiments to demonstrate the competitiveness of the proposed architectures, which falls under the scientific computing (cs.SI) sub-category.
